 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/02 7:35:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=698.topic&index=76>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Soloing Mages</span><hr size=1> Its gone now but I did an analysis of soloing with a Mage and with a Wizard, comparing the two.  It was called Quad Kiting with a Magician, and the comparison was of a Magician soloing successive blues until he had to stop vs a Wizard soloing 4 blues at a time then having to stop.  The overall xp gain was roughly equivalent (particuarly as the Mage could make his own focus gear).  Mages had some advantages and limitations unique to them, so did Wizards.  Overall, the classes were equal soloing, at least in that level range.  Earlier, Mages solo better, later, Wizards do.  Soloing is a non-issue as far as these two classes are concerned, in my opinion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/02 2:20:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=698.topic&index=77>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing Mages</span><hr size=1> I did a teoretical compare of mage with pet and kiting wizard on a thread on the magicians tower:<br>
<br>
First some asumptions to make it clearer and easier to argue against this note:<br>
<br>
As a magician its generaly not that efficient xp to outdamage the pet to get full xp. -&gt; So I will compare the xp gotten when using this less efficient magician tactic to quad kiting.<br>
<br>
To get full xp the magician needs to do more damag then the pet, but the DS will not be attributed to either. There will also be a margin of error in maybe not knowing exactly how much damage to do. -&gt; So the DS damage will give the margin of error needed for the mage.<br>
<br>
Both classes have support spells needed to be cast like DS and snare, but they wont be included in the calculations.<br>
<br>
The resist rate of quad kiting spells are not as low as on wizard nukes, so the resist rate for either class will be asumed to be near same.<br>
<br>
The will be some mobs for the magician to kill somewhere that doesnt hurt the pet harder then that it can heal as fast as the magician meditates when he outdamage the pet.<br>
<br>
Buffs, skills and focus items wont be factored in.<br>
<br>
<br>
Then to make some comparisons based on those asumptions:<br>
<br>
Quadkiting wizard damage/mana using best pre 50 spell: 4.9<br>
Magician damage/mana using best pre 50 spell to outdamage pet: 5.4<br>
<br>
Quadkiting wizard damage/mana using best post 50 spell: 10.5<br>
Magician damage/mana using best post 50 damagespell to outdamage pet: 9.5<br>
<br>
And the same for wizards not quad kiting, but this will get less resists:<br>
Singlekiting wizard damage/mana using best pre 50 spell: 2.8<br>
Singlekiting wizard damage/mana using best post 50 spell: 4.0<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/02 4:28:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=698.topic&index=78>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grim3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing Mages</span><hr size=1> The comparisons I did were from actual play in the game.  I sat and killed 4 monsters before my mana and the pet's hps were low enough I had to stop, and it was about the same time as killing 4 creatures quad kiting with a Wizard - from finding the target to getting all mana back.  The mana use from the Mage was lower, but had to factor in the pet's hps.  Mages can solo places Wizards can't dare to, clear out greens better, and solo at lower level.  Wizards are more survivable by a slight margin (not as great as some Mages want to portray), move around better, and deal with adds more succesfully.  Overall it was a draw. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usilverbladetheenchanter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silverblade the Enchanter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/02 4:58:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=698.topic&index=79>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.silverblades-suitcase.com/artofadreamer/3d/excaliburthumb1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing Mages</span><hr size=1> Best way to solo as a mage actually, is to chain cast.<br>
The big problem mages face is that pets take xp if they out damage, but over burning blows mana (higher resists maybe fizzles to? since we specialize in EITHER fire or magic nukes, not both, compared to a wiz)<br>
<br>
So what you do is pull the mob, sic pet, usually an earth pet. It maybe buffed, when pet's low in health and you are in command range, you start casting another pet, and pre-type /pet get lost . At last fraction of spell, say 1/3rd bubb, you hit enter key, old pet that's badly damaged is replaced by a new one. When mob is low health you can Reclaim Energy pet, and nuke-kill mob for full xp.<br>
<br>
very very efficient, for example its 325 mana for my 1005 hp nuke, or 400 mana for 57 earth pet.<br>
<br>
However it is *not* easy  bad connection, lag, any screw up and you have no pet and a very POd mob.<br>
<br>
Redorious<br>
Archmage<br>
